<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER BLOWER WITH STANDARD
        TEMPERATURE CONTROL (SLEEPER) - TROUBLESHOOTING - STANDARD TEMPERATURE CONTROL (SLEEPER)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>STANDARD TEMPERATURE CONTROL (SLEEPER)</title>
        <table id="t0828303" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Standard Temperature Control (Sleeper)</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.85in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.87in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.29in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (552), and move key switch to ignition position. At (552) circuit
                                75AL, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), 75AL to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75AL, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (552) measure voltage from circuit 75AL to 75-GS.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), 75AL to 75-GS.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-GS, 11-GBJ, 11-GAN, conn. (81), or
                                circuit 11-GBB to right cab gnd. stud (404), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (552) and pigtail to sleeper temperature control, measure resistance from
                                terminal A to C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), term. A to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>9K ohms to 11K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective sleeper temperature control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (552) and pigtail to sleeper temperature control, measure resistance from
                                terminal B to C with control rotated fully CCW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), term. B to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>39K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective sleeper temperature control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (552) and pigtail to sleeper temperature control, measure resistance from
                                terminal A to B with control rotated fully CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(552), term. A to B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>39K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective sleeper temperature control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (552), disconnect heater box conn. (45), move key switch to
                                ignition position, and at (45) circuit 75K [going to (80)] measure voltage to ground
                                while rotating sleeper temp. control fully CCW and CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(45), 75K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>2V and 11V.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75K, connector (80) or circuit 75K, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (45) measure voltage from circuit 75L [coming from (441)] to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(45), 75L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (45). Does heater box damper door function properly? (Damper door
                                should open and close with temperature control, and close when sleeper blower switch is
                                moved to off position.)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to Step 13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect heater box damper conn. (N/L) and with key switch in ignition position,
                                measure voltage from circuit 75L to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(N/L), 75L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At heater box damper connector (N/L), measure voltage from circuit 75L to 75-GL.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(N/L), 75L to 75-GL</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-GL, conn. (44), circuit 75-G or 11-G to
                                right cab gnd. stud (404), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At heater box damper conn. (N/L), with sleeper blower switch (55) in low position,
                                measure voltage from circuit 75K to ground while rotating sleeper temperature control
                                fully CCW and CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(N/L), 75K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>2V and 11V.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect heater box damper conn. (N/L), move key switch to ignition position, and
                                place sleeper blower switch (550) in low speed position. Note if damper door closes
                                completely and opens completely, when sleeper temp. control is moved fully CW and CCW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective damper motor assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Sleeper temperature control circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
